## TOPs Frameset Images to Image Sequence

### Example HIP: 

* TOPs\_Frameset\_Images\_to\_Image\_Sequence\_V001.hip]

### Description:

Use Houdini TOPs to extract frameset images back into flat image sequences.

The images are copied from a "frameset" folder that is formatted as:  

	"$HIP/images/####/Camera.NNNN.tiff"

This input is formatted like:  

	"$HIP/images/[0001-0153]/Camera.[0001-200].tif"

The output is a flat image sequence placed in a single folder: 
 
	"$HIP/images/Camera_NNNN.####.tiff"

The symbols "\#\#\#\#" represent the image sequence frame number.  
The symbols "NNNN" represent the camera array view number.

This results in an end output that looks  like:  

	"$HIP/images/Camera_[0001-0153].[0001-200].tif"

### TOPs Node Parameters:

#### File Pattern Node

Files Type: Files Only  
Pattern: $HIP/images/0001/\*.tiff

Outputs:  
\[x\] Output Attribute: filesTIFF  
\[x\] Output File Tag: file/image

#### Attribute from String Node

Source String:\`@filesTIFF\`  
Operation: Match by Pattern  
Pattern Type: Simple Pattern  
Pattern: Camera.{ViewName:string}.tiff  
![][image33]

#### Range Generate Node

Specify Range As: Value Range  
Value Range: 2-153 ("Right click \> Delete Channels" to unlock the number inputs)  
\[x\] Inclusive  
Store Value as: Custom Attribute  
Attribute Name: rangeValue  
\[x\] Set Range Attribute: range

Note: Set the "End Frame" range value to line up with the number of frames in the image sequence.
